      "id": "book01-down-the-rabbit-hole",
      "name": "DOWN THE RABBIT HOLE",
      "level": 1,
      "category": "booklet",
      "sort_order": 1,
      "sections": {
        "Page 1": "ALICE WAS SITTING BY THE RIVER.\nSHE WAS VERY, VERY BORED.",
        "Page 2": "THEN A WHITE RABBIT RAN BY.\n\"OH DEAR! I SHALL BE LATE!\"\nSAID THE RABBIT.",
        "Page 3": "ALICE JUMPED UP AND RAN AFTER HIM.\nTHE RABBIT JUMPED INTO A BIG HOLE.",
        "Page 4": "ALICE JUMPED IN TOO.\nSHE FELL DOWN, DOWN, DOWN.\nPAST SHELVES AND MAPS AND JARS.",
        "Page 5": "SHE LANDED IN A HALL WITH MANY DOORS.\nON A TABLE THERE WAS A TINY BOTTLE.\nIT SAID: \"DRINK ME.\"",
        "Page 6": "ALICE DRANK IT AND GOT VERY SMALL!\nTHEN SHE ATE A CAKE THAT SAID \"EAT ME.\"\nAND SHE GREW VERY, VERY BIG!"
      },
