      "id": "book06-the-cheshire-cat",
      "name": "THE CHESHIRE CAT",
      "level": 1,
      "category": "booklet",
      "sort_order": 6,
      "sections": {
        "Page 1": "ALICE CAME TO A LITTLE HOUSE.\nA FISH GAVE A LETTER TO A FROG.\nINSIDE, A COOK WAS MAKING SOUP.\nTHERE WAS TOO MUCH PEPPER!",
        "Page 2": "THE DUCHESS HAD A BABY.\n\"HERE, HOLD HIM!\" SHE SAID.\nALICE TOOK THE BABY OUTSIDE.\nBUT HE TURNED INTO A PIG!",
        "Page 3": "\"WELL!\" SAID ALICE.\n\"HE MAKES A BETTER PIG THAN A BABY.\"\nSHE LET HIM GO.",
        "Page 4": "THEN SHE SAW A BIG CAT IN A TREE.\nHE WAS GRINNING FROM EAR TO EAR.\n\"WE ARE ALL MAD HERE,\" SAID THE CAT.\nTHEN HE DISAPPEARED — BUT HIS GRIN STAYED!"
