    {
      "id": "book07-the-mad-tea-party",
      "name": "THE MAD TEA PARTY",
      "level": 1,
      "category": "booklet",
      "sort_order": 7,
      "sections": {
        "Page 1": "ALICE FOUND A TEA PARTY.\nTHE MAD HATTER, THE MARCH HARE,\nAND THE DORMOUSE SAT AT A BIG TABLE.\n\"NO ROOM! NO ROOM!\" THEY SAID.",
        "Page 2": "\"WHY IS A RAVEN LIKE A WRITING DESK?\"\nASKED THE HATTER.\n\"I DON'T KNOW,\" SAID ALICE.\n\"I DON'T KNOW EITHER!\" SAID THE HATTER.",
        "Page 3": "THE HATTER HAD A BROKEN WATCH.\nIT TOLD THE DAY BUT NOT THE TIME.\n\"IT IS ALWAYS SIX O'CLOCK,\" HE SAID.\n\"IT IS ALWAYS TEA-TIME.\"",
        "Page 4": "\"TELL US A STORY!\" THEY SAID TO THE DORMOUSE.\n\"ONCE THERE WERE THREE SISTERS...\nTHEY LIVED IN A WELL...\"\nTHE DORMOUSE FELL ASLEEP.",
        "Page 5": "\"THIS IS THE SILLIEST TEA PARTY EVER!\"\nSAID ALICE.\nSHE GOT UP AND WALKED AWAY.\n\"I AM NEVER COMING BACK!\""
      },
